The paper examines the strategies of social bots on Twitter during a mass shooting event, which involves analyzing social media data and using qualitative and quantitative methods. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, given the focus on social bots and their strategies, cs.SI and cs.CY are the most likely sub-categories.
